    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In traditional Indian art and dance, a squatting or sitting figural pose, often with one leg raised. An example of usage is to represent deities in an angry aspect.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
